  "author": "Gary Marcus",
  "siteName": "Marcus on AI",
  "content": "<html>\n <head></head>\n <body>\n  <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n   <figure>\n    <a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_53301dda-44ba-40b4-84c5-7b88ef58c79b_1153x600.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"> \n     <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n      <picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5ba5d5c1-a04c-4e61-4d46-6b7ed4c81900/public 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_53301dda-44ba-40b4-84c5-7b88ef58c79b_1153x600.png 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5dcbdc9f-c953-41b2-1e31-22339be32b00/public 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_53301dda-44ba-40b4-84c5-7b88ef58c79b_1153x600.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5a7272ad-4b67-473c-e50c-23012fc4d800/public\" width=\"1153\" height=\"600\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/53301dda-44ba-40b4-84c5-7b88ef58c79b_1153x600.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:600,&quot;width&quot;:1153,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:100909,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://garymarcus.substack.com/i/190531162?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F53301dda-44ba-40b4-84c5-7b88ef58c79b_1153x600.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_53301dda-44ba-40b4-84c5-7b88ef58c79b_1153x600.png 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_53301dda-44ba-40b4-84c5-7b88ef58c79b_1153x600.png 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5595e485-3356-4bf0-d906-8f473d538d00/public 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/5a7272ad-4b67-473c-e50c-23012fc4d800/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" fetchpriority=\"high\"></picture>\n      <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n       <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n        <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n         <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n          <g>\n           <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n          </g>\n         </svg>\n        </button>\n        <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n         <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n          <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n         </svg>\n        </button>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n     </div> \n    </a>\n   </figure>\n  </div>\n  <p>Just in the last few years alone, cancer has taken <a href=\"https://open.substack.com/pub/garymarcus/p/marilyn-molly-marcus-1942-2026?utm_campaign=post-expanded-share&amp;utm_medium=web\">my mother</a>, one of my closest friends from childhood, <a href=\"https://garymarcus.substack.com/p/karen-bakker-1971-2023?utm_source=publication-search\">my closest friend</a> in my adopted hometown (she was only 51), and a beloved aunt who inspired and supported me throughout my life<a class=\"footnote-anchor\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteAnchorToDOM\" id=\"footnote-anchor-1\" href=\"#footnote-1\" target=\"_self\">1</a>, as well as several colleagues, including the AI pioneer <a href=\"https://open.substack.com/pub/garymarcus/p/doug-lenat-1950-2023?utm_campaign=post-expanded-share&amp;utm_medium=web\">Doug Lenat</a>. And of course my own experience is far from unique; virtually everyone I know has lost loved ones to cancer.</p>\n  <p>AI is supposed to change all that. But so far it hasn’t.</p>\n  <p>A <a href=\"https://curecancer.ai/#\">new essay</a> by Emilia Javorsky, a physician scientist at the Future of Life Institute, offers a sobering statistic:</p>\n  <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n   <figure>\n    <a class=\"image-link image2\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_32b1a42f-1d6a-4a4e-b32f-02d6d5d40d62_1284x283.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"> \n     <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n      <picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_32b1a42f-1d6a-4a4e-b32f-02d6d5d40d62_1284x283.png 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/1610a089-3035-4021-4e8e-887d0749bc00/public 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!fTC7!,w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1a42f-1d6a-4a4e-b32f-02d6d5d40d62_1284x283.png 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_32b1a42f-1d6a-4a4e-b32f-02d6d5d40d62_1284x283.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_32b1a42f-1d6a-4a4e-b32f-02d6d5d40d62_1284x283.png\" width=\"1284\" height=\"283\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/32b1a42f-1d6a-4a4e-b32f-02d6d5d40d62_1284x283.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:283,&quot;width&quot;:1284,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:40020,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://garymarcus.substack.com/i/190531162?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F32b1a42f-1d6a-4a4e-b32f-02d6d5d40d62_1284x283.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_32b1a42f-1d6a-4a4e-b32f-02d6d5d40d62_1284x283.png 424w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/34c7fe99-cb6a-4375-d215-62f30cbca400/public 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_32b1a42f-1d6a-4a4e-b32f-02d6d5d40d62_1284x283.png 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_32b1a42f-1d6a-4a4e-b32f-02d6d5d40d62_1284x283.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"></picture>\n      <div></div>\n     </div> \n    </a>\n   </figure>\n  </div>\n  <p>I don’t agree with everything in the new essay, but I agree with a lot of it. The part that I agree with most is its strong objection to technosolutionism, to the kind of fantasy that if we just had the right algorithm, cancer would be magically and immediately solved. (Dario Amodei’s ridiculous claims about doubling life span in the next decade are deluded on this front.)</p>\n  <p>Javorsky writes, for example, that</p>\n  <blockquote>\n   <p>“Silicon Valley has repeatedly stormed into healthcare with the hubris of outsiders attempting to reinvent a system they do not fully understand, failing to learn from past mistakes. The repeated pattern suggests not mere execution challenges but systemic misunderstanding of what’s actually limiting medical progress.”</p>\n  </blockquote>\n  <p>As Javorsky argues. sometimes failures in the drug development market have more to do with market forces than science. For example, Javorsky notes that “New antibiotics are inherently unprofitable, as they must be used sparingly to avoid promoting resistance, limiting revenue potential.” That’s not a science problem, it’s an incentives problem.</p>\n  <p>Or a disease may be too rare, or drug too expensive to produce. Or a looming patent expiration deadline might lead a company to abandon costly studies of a drug that actually works, simply because the economics aren’t promising enough. Javorsky gives the example of Tanespimycin, which was “difficult to produce [with] only limited time remaining before the drug’s patent expires [making] further investment in the drug difficult to justify financially.\" Even if we had perfect AI, it would only be part of the battle.</p>\n  <p>§</p>\n  <p>Javorsky is also quite right that there is – and always has been – a great deal of naivete:</p>\n  <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n   <figure>\n    <a class=\"image-link image2 is-viewable-img\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_b2bc871b-eb8b-4f29-83af-615be8dd231e_1407x1288.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"> \n     <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n      <picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/bb08dc57-f5da-4880-8391-dfd56218a600/public 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_b2bc871b-eb8b-4f29-83af-615be8dd231e_1407x1288.png 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_b2bc871b-eb8b-4f29-83af-615be8dd231e_1407x1288.png 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/6631b2ee-1985-41be-81ae-4d1af15fb300/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/57428eda-4ab5-4d60-e8a1-f0da6787b100/public\" width=\"1407\" height=\"1288\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/b2bc871b-eb8b-4f29-83af-615be8dd231e_1407x1288.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:1288,&quot;width&quot;:1407,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:298151,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://garymarcus.substack.com/i/190531162?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fb2bc871b-eb8b-4f29-83af-615be8dd231e_1407x1288.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/fc424bb4-7712-429f-7db8-982987154a00/public 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_b2bc871b-eb8b-4f29-83af-615be8dd231e_1407x1288.png 848w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_b2bc871b-eb8b-4f29-83af-615be8dd231e_1407x1288.png 1272w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/57428eda-4ab5-4d60-e8a1-f0da6787b100/public 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\"></picture>\n      <div class=\"image-link-expand\">\n       <div class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\">\n        <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\">\n         <svg role=\"img\" style=\"height:20px;width:20px\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\">\n          <g>\n           <title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path>\n          </g>\n         </svg>\n        </button>\n        <button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\">\n         <svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\">\n          <polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line>\n         </svg>\n        </button>\n       </div>\n      </div>\n     </div> \n    </a>\n   </figure>\n  </div>\n  <p>Javorsky cautions against oversimplifying biology:</p>\n  <div class=\"captioned-image-container\">\n   <figure>\n    <a class=\"image-link image2\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_93136204-057c-42df-8d4d-1495014f30e6_1343x178.png\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOM\"> \n     <div class=\"image2-inset\">\n      <picture><source type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/c845be43-bb05-4ab1-2e2f-0d195d434500/public 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_93136204-057c-42df-8d4d-1495014f30e6_1343x178.png 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/ed6d8da8-9e11-4d0f-02a8-15e07d31b300/public 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_93136204-057c-42df-8d4d-1495014f30e6_1343x178.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\"><img src=\"https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_93136204-057c-42df-8d4d-1495014f30e6_1343x178.png\" width=\"1343\" height=\"178\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/93136204-057c-42df-8d4d-1495014f30e6_1343x178.png&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:178,&quot;width&quot;:1343,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:28176,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/png&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:&quot;https://garymarcus.substack.com/i/190531162?img=https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F93136204-057c-42df-8d4d-1495014f30e6_1343x178.png&quot;,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" class=\"sizing-normal\" alt=\"\" srcset=\"https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/0c7665d7-f62a-48f1-7860-b333445a2800/public 424w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_93136204-057c-42df-8d4d-1495014f30e6_1343x178.png 848w, https://imagedelivery.net/qGOFcc1O8XwTZW3W1JAHHg/e0af79e1-ded8-4475-7bcc-46f8cc1b3200/public 1272w, https://image.jido.dev/20260316230031_93136204-057c-42df-8d4d-1495014f30e6_1343x178.png 1456w\" sizes=\"100vw\" loading=\"lazy\"></picture>\n      <div></div>\n     </div> \n    </a>\n   </figure>\n  </div>\n  <p>As a friend of mine likes to say, “that was never going to work.”</p>\n  <p>The reality is that biology is really really hard. Our bodies are made of trillions of interacting molecules, and each body is different. Many drugs that work for some people (probably) fail clinical trials because they work on some subset of people but we don’t understand biology well enough to know which is which.</p>\n  <p>§</p>\n  <p>The one thing I think Javorsky gets somewhat wrong is that she downplays just how important getting the right algorithm is, and how far we are from that point.</p>\n  <p>At the risk of redundancy, I will repeat a quote I shared recently from Eli Lilly CEO David Ricks in a different context that is very much on topic:</p>\n  <blockquote>\n   <p>[AI is far from curing cancer and most other diseases.] If you just ask them to solve biology or chemistry questions, they’re not particularly good at it… They’re trained on the human language, not on the language of chemistry, physics, and biology.”</p>\n  </blockquote>\n  <p>Over and over we discover drugs with AI that work on trials in animals but not safely enough in humans; we just don’t understand biology well enough. (This isn’t a problem specific to AI. According to one analysis, <a href=\"https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/02611929231157756\">92% of all drug trials that work with animals have toxicity problems in humans</a>.)</p>\n  <p>Actually beating cancer is going to require systemic changes, both technical and economic, in how we develop and test drugs, as Javorsky convincingly argues, but also deeper forms of artificial intelligence that are better able to reason about chemistry, physics and biology.<a class=\"footnote-anchor\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteAnchorToDOM\" id=\"footnote-anchor-2\" href=\"#footnote-2\" target=\"_self\">2</a> AI will also need <a href=\"https://x.com/lefthanddraft/status/2033577766155862215?s=61\">to sweat the details</a> a whole lot better.</p>\n  <p>The sooner we get there the better.</p>\n  <p><em>This essay is written in memory of my mother, who would have been 84 last week, my memory of my father, taken by cancer over decade ago, and all the other friends and colleagues and relatives that I have lost, and in memory of all those that we all have lost. </em></p>\n  <div class=\"footnote\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOM\">\n   <a id=\"footnote-1\" href=\"#footnote-anchor-1\" class=\"footnote-number\" contenteditable=\"false\" target=\"_self\">1</a>\n   <div class=\"footnote-content\">\n    <p>As it happens, I honored Aunt Esther in one of the most important passages in my books, featuring her in a hypothetical that anticipated the problem of hallucinations in 2001, in <em>The Algebraic Mind</em>.</p>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"footnote\" data-component-name=\"FootnoteToDOM\">\n   <a id=\"footnote-2\" href=\"#footnote-anchor-2\" class=\"footnote-number\" contenteditable=\"false\" target=\"_self\">2</a>\n   <div class=\"footnote-content\">\n    <p>Of course AI can have a positive impact on medical research long before it reaches that level of sophistication, simply by streamlining everyday tasks, helping with subject recruitment and paperwork, and so on; such productivity gains seem plausible in the short-term, even if the more dramatic magic some people are hoping for doesn’t. In the near-term, the greatest contributions from AI towards combating disease will probably come from enhancing humans with better tools rather than radical new scientific discovery.</p>\n    <p></p>\n   </div>\n  </div>\n </body>\n</html>",
  "aiSummary": "Gary Marcus 讨论了当前 AI 方法在解决癌症治疗等复杂问题时的局限性和风险。",
